verbose_text: Spore forming, gram positive anaerobic bacillus with terminal spores (C. tetani has terminal spores) Mechanism : Tetanospasmin toxin causes tetany by inhibiting the release of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) from cerebellum, and glycine from Renshaw cells of spinal cord.
